The article discusses a provision in the Wall Street Reform and Consumer Protection Act that requires energy and mining companies registered with the U.S. Securities and Exchange Commission to disclose their payments to foreign countries and the U.S. government for oil, gas, and minerals. This provision aims to promote transparency in the oil and mineral sectors by providing citizens with information to monitor companies and hold governments accountable. It also sets a new standard for corporate transparency. The United States plans to work with other countries to implement similar disclosure requirements in other financial markets.